sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Internal CA
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Workbench

    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/lab<br/>HTTPS Request
    Router->>OAuth: Forward Request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Internal TLS
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OpenShift OAuth Token
    alt Authentication Required
        OAuth-->>User: Redirect to OAuth Login
        User->>OAuth: Authenticate with OpenShift
    end
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward Request<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>Localhost (no encryption)
    Jupyter->>Jupyter: Serve JupyterLab UI
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: HTML Response
    OAuth-->>Router: Forward Response
    Router-->>User: Encrypted HTTPS Response

    Note over User,S3: User Loads Data from Object Storage

    User->>Router: POST /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/api/contents<br/>Load data request
    Router->>OAuth: Forward Request (8443/TCP HTTPS)
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward Request (8888/TCP HTTP)
    Jupyter->>S3: GET /bucket/data.csv<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>S3 Credentials Auth
    S3-->>Jupyter: Data File
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: JSON Response
    OAuth-->>Router: Forward Response
    Router-->>User: Data Loaded

    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipeline Controller
    participant Runtime as Runtime Container<br/>(Pod)
    participant KFP_API as Kubeflow API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over KFP,KFP_API: Flow 2: Kubeflow Pipeline Task Execution

    KFP->>Runtime: Create Pod with Runtime Image<br/>ServiceAccount Token Auth
    Runtime->>Runtime: Execute Pipeline Task Code
    Runtime->>S3: GET /bucket/model.pkl<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>Runtime: Model Artifact
    Runtime->>Runtime: Process Data / Train Model
    Runtime->>S3: PUT /bucket/output.pkl<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>AWS SigV4 Auth
    S3-->>Runtime: Upload Success
    Runtime->>KFP_API: POST /apis/v1/artifacts<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    KFP_API-->>Runtime: Artifact Registered
    Runtime-->>KFP: Task Complete (Exit Code 0)

    participant Konflux as Konflux Pipeline
    participant GitHub as GitHub Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant UBI_Reg as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Quay_Push as Quay.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant IS as OpenShift ImageStream

    Note over Konflux,IS: Flow 3: Image Build and Deployment

    Konflux->>GitHub: Clone Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Git Token Auth
    GitHub-->>Konflux: Source Code
    Konflux->>UBI_Reg: Pull UBI9 Python Base Image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Pull Secret Auth
    UBI_Reg-->>Konflux: Base Image
    Konflux->>Konflux: Build Container Image<br/>Multi-arch (x86_64, arm64, ppc64le, s390x)
    Konflux->>Konflux: Security Scan (Trivy/Clair)
    Konflux->>Quay_Push: Push Image<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+<br/>Push Secret Auth
    Quay_Push-->>Konflux: Image Pushed
    Konflux->>IS: Update ImageStream Reference<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Kubeconfig Auth
    IS-->>Konflux: ImageStream Updated
    Note over IS: Image now available for deployment
